AGI -&nbsp; The last hypothesis of crime that was challenged to him, that of corruption, vanished a few days ago to six years from when he learned it. At the request of the Procura, the gip of Busto Arsizio filed it underlining the "unfounded event of the news of crime". In the meantime, the life of Giuseppe Filoni, at the time president of a public body for the purification of the waters in the province of Varese and the leader of a cooperative that billed 5 million a year, was stritolata by the investigation 'Mensa dei Poveri' carried out by the Procura di Milano that hypothesized its participation in a large system of piloted contracts, corruption and illegal financing with the involvement of politicians.
"It was as if all of a sudden I had been catapulted on Mars - Filoni told AGI&nbsp;- in the sense that if I was 'organized', taking into consideration the hypothesis of committing crimes as some entrepreneurs do, I would have taken it into account. Instead I ended up on Mars and I didn't know how to behave on that planet." &nbsp;>
Step back. When in 2019 there were 43 arrests, Filoni was investigated for office abuse, a crime that was then modified in bribery because, in the guise of the sole administrator of the public society that presided over, he was suspected of having entrusted assignments to Alberto Bilardo, also involved in the investigation, entrusted in violation of the correct procedures. He was then accused and acquitted 'because the fact does not exist' from the treasury of aast>a for the management of the bar of the hospital of Busto Arsizio two years ago. In the meantime, the corruption file has been transmitted by territorial jurisdiction from Milan to Busto Arsizio and, a year after the request for storage, the end word has arrived.
"You were years ago I was a 44-year-old man in the middle of my career - rewinds the Filoni tape -. When I heard of being investigated, I decided to defend myself, taking part in the hearings, questioning me and constantly asking my lawyer (Lara Paladino, ndr) what was going on. I was president under renewal of a body for water purification and, when all began, the municipalities were deciding my renewal. Before they asked me, I decided to take a step back and not embarrass them." > &nbsp;
He also decided to leave the service cooperative of which he was president: "Rightly or right, customers began to cancel their orders. No one ever disputed me about the merits of work but disregarded or with generic motivations or not renewing at the expiry. They labeled me. The company billed 5 million a year and chose to resign in 2020 so as not to damage it even more by my name." Suddenly, he summarizes, "I was found by entrepreneur to criminal and I suffered a lot, more than for work, as a person. At the level of family relationships and friendship I 'expanded', as it is natural, my problem to whom I was close. At the economic level with what I had on my side I managed to stay afloat. Now I don't sail in gold, but I'm in.> I'm a match consultant Iva, I follow safety, work and training, taking advantage of the experience gained over the years, and I'm serene."
After archiving, he feels he's taken out "a swan." "After so many years between courts, I can say that the worst aspect is the long wait to get justice, in addition to the media massacre. But I'm 50 years old, they say it's the age in which the 'second time' begins and I look forward with confidence." &nbsp;
